      • checkData

        private boolean checkData(java.lang.String[] data)
        This method checks the validity of loaded data.

        There are five elements included in an order, as specified in PARAMS_LIST. Each of them is validated with a regular expression. The requestId, quantity and price values are checked with use of isStringLong(String), isStringInt(String) and isStringBigDecimal(String) methods to see if they can be parsed into the corresponding types.

        The data fields are validated as follows: 

           clientId - should be an alphanumeric String without spaces,
              not longer than 6 characters.
   requestId - should be a type of Long.
   name - should be an alphanumeric String with spaces,
          not longer than 255 characters.
   quantity - should be a type of Integer.
   price - should be a type of BigDecimal with double precision and total
           number of digits equal to 12.
        Parameters:
        data - an array of type String which contains data of loaded order.
        Returns:
        true if the provided data is valid.
        See Also:
        isStringLong(String), isStringInt(String), isStringBigDecimal(String)
